        {
          "id": "step3",
          "action": "While the mushrooms are in the oven, mix together the remaining 2 tablespoons of olive oil with the remaining 0.25 tsp of cinnamon, 1 crushed garlic clove, the chilli flakes, and 0.25 tsp of flaked salt. Brush the oil and spices over one side of the brioche slices and place on a separate parchment-lined baking tray, brushed side up. With about 6 or 7 minutes left for the mushrooms, put the bread into the oven alongside the mushrooms and roast until the bread is golden-brown and crisp.",
